#- §lForeword§0
§0
§0   §0Aurora was built very early on in the history of 2.0. For many months it was in the top 3 of the Civcraft Activity Index, and was known as one of the "Big 3" cities alongside Orion and §0CommonWealth.The§0 purpose of this book 
#- is to give the world a glimpse into the history and popular lore within this great civilization. Without further ado, I present to you...
#- §lChapter 1: §0§nThe §0§nJewel of the Plus §0§nMinus§0
§0
§0   §0The first days of Civcraft 2.0 were a mad dash. Groups all over the server had been planning their cities for weeks in anticipation of the start of the new world. There were plans for a quadrant
#- meetup spot located at +3k -3k. Players from all backgrounds made their way to this quaint little town and began their adventures. Some players went off mining and struck rich, while others searched for suitable locations to found their cities. The New
#- Agorans scouted for over a week until a location was finally found at +4200 -1600.§0
§0
§0   A large bay surrounbed by forest for as far as the eye could see with a tiny testificate village on the west side.T he first few citizens to 
#- reach the location built houses on the beach of the bay, while Tambien_Sinclair began construction on the massive terrace walls that are still in place today. The leadership struggled to control the random buildingoccuring around the area, but as the days
#- went on the first roads and plots were laid. Things progressed quickly at this point and the downtown district sprang into existence. Throughout this book, various links will be provided to enhance the reader's experience. Please type out the links to 
#- follow along.§0
§0§limgur.com/IFMKgxO§0§l §0This picture shows the first houses that were built.§0
§0§limgur.com/aO7pATaHere§0§l §0is another view showing the opposite side of the bay.§0
§0§limgur.com/il63fyh§0
§0Early Render§0
§0§limgur.com/zc1FjJ4§0
§0Docks Render§0

