#- §lChapter Two: §0§nThe §0§nFederation§0
§0
§0   §0Aurora was to be the capital of the Agoran Federation. This Federation held many provinces throughout its time, including Muutang Resort, Luxerion Island, Bohr Island, Alkaowni Province, and 
#- Moonraker. The government was set up by a constitution that required officials to be voted in by the citizens of the Federation. The main positions and Aurora's first official in each was as follows: Chemistry35 as Chancellor; farley50 as Secretary of the
#- Interior; Galvan_ as Secretary of Peace; Orikbise as Secretary of Education. The Secretary of the Interior was resposible for all infrastructure within and around Aurora. They were not alone in this, however, as many citizens gave their time 
#- to construction.
#- §lChapter Three: §0§l§nBuilding the City§0
§0
§0   §0AgentMuu built a large public farm northwest of Aurora that is still in use today. Originally quite far from the city, urban sprawl quickly overtook it.§0
§0§limgur.com/7QYYkgY§0§l §0Picture of early 
#- district planning.§0
§0§limgur.com/AfSKS1E§0§l §0This is the earliest known picture of the town square.§0
§0
§0   The South District, with the help of Hummelwagen who oversaw the construction, became a farmer's district with ranch houses and 
#- larger plot sizes. It later on seceeded from the Federation. The East District was created by PeppermintPig as an industrial district in which the city could centralize its factories. The University project was begun by Orikibise, and taken over by 
#- Ogel6000. This area flourished in design and architecture and was intended to be used as an ingame university. The West District was originally designed by Pantostado1600 to be a small town-themed neighborhood, but was later utilized as a district for new
#- players. The North District was built around the northwest peninsula and surrounded AgentMuu's farm.
#- §lChapter Four: §0§nThe §0§nRedHats§0
§0
§0   §0Early in the history of Civcraft 2.0, settlements across the world had a lot of trouble with griefers and raiders. This, coupled with the inactivity of the Secretary of Peace caused much strife. In 
#- order to fill the void in leadership, farley50 created the Ruff Howsers. Commonly referred to as the "RedHats" because of their iconic red leather hats, the Ruff Howser Gang quickly gained support throughout Aurora and became the first line ofdefense
#- against attacks of all kinds. Conspiracy theorists were convinced the RedHats secretly controlled the government behind the scenes using elected officials as puppets to further their needs. As time went on and Aurora became better equipped to defend 
#- itself, the RedHats began to take a back seat role and moved out of the spotlight. Hidden signs and symbols can still be found throughout the city today, and it has been said that adventurers who lose their way in Aurora's vast undercity speak tales of
#- stumbling across the old RedHat club house: §0§limgur.com/Ralqt1S§0§l §0§limgur.com/2l3FLwh§0§l §0§limgur.com/1u5msp5§0§l §0§limgur.com/nB1BpF6
#- §lChapter Five: §0§l§nHistorical Events§0
§0§nThe Alkaowni Betrayal:§0
§0   §0Long ago, in 1.0, New Agora had but one main enemy: Mandy. Mandy was the leader of a terrorist cell named the Alkaowni. This groupterrorized New Agora by placing multiple stacks of DRO 
#- grief throughout the city in a matter of a few hours. New Agora spent three days camping the logout of Mandy until Mandy finally logged in and was pearled by farley50. With the beginning of a new map, the New Agorans chose to invite the group to town in
#- order to start fresh and try out a different play style. The Alkaowni played nice for a few weeks and even helped build a vault and sell xp. Finally, one day the Alkaowni griefed Aurora with over 7 stacks of DRO; an attack so devastating that it
#- singlehandedly brought about the creation of the Acid Block. After a month of work, the DRO was gone and Aurora moved on.§0
§0
§0§nThe Mirango Incident:§0
§0   §0Around the time of the conception of the South District, three new players came and 
#- settled in Aurora: Hummelwagen, SexyBunny, and Mirandasquish. These three also began constructionon the 'Mirango Co-op' which happened to be on the edge of the Bryn continent. This resulted in a long winded dispute in which members of the co-op 
#- were pearled, causing tension between Bryn and Aurora. Finally, the co-op members were released and eventually all involved became friends.§0
§0
§0§nThe Old Guard Exodus:§0
§0   §0Also around this time something interesting began to happen. The 1.0 New 
#- Agorans (commonly referred to as the 'Old Guard') who planned and founded the city of Aurora began to butt heads with new players that were starting to take on bigger roles throughout the city. Plot disagreements and arguments about the inefficiency of
#- the government quickly created a fissure between most of the Old Guard and Aurora's emerging leaders. This finally came to a head when a large group of the Old Agorans decided to leave the city. Though this event was tragic, Aurora continued to 
#- grow and thrive in the coming months.§0
§0
§0§nFriedrich Dissolves §0§nthe Government:§0
§0   §0When the Old Guard left, the city of Aurora had elected FriedrichHayek into office. His main goal was to rework the constitution along with other core members 
#- of the city in order to resolve redudancies and create a new charter. Finally, a charter was completed and governmental positions changed. This event was the final nail in the coffin of the federal government, causing Aurora to become increasingly more 
#- Anarcho-Capitalist in nature.§0
§0
§0§nThe Separation of the §0§nTownsfolk:§0
§0   §0 After a few more months of peace and prosperity, the HCF became a clear and present danger to the server. Around this time, many Citizens became inactive either 
#- out of boredom or real life commitments, and most of the core members of the city went off to fight the HCF while others moved to Fellowship or on to different projects.
#- §lChapter Six: §0§nPop §0§nCulture§0
§0
§0   §0Upon learning the amount of breaks a single piece of DRO requires, an Auroran citizen proclaimed "1800?! JESUS". This phrase became well known throughout the city and even spawned a religion.§0

#- 
§0   During the Mirango Incident, signs were placed to claim territory much to the disapproval of Bryn. In response, Brynian citizens acquired a plot within Aurora and proceeded to place "Sign is God" signs allover the plot. The "Sign is God" meme 
#- eventually became a religion as well.§0
§0
§0   The Owluminati were responsible for building the Auroran National park. There have been many rumors of hidden rooms and even a full-sized Inn hidden within the park itself.§0
§0

#-    "Now that I am elected, I'll see you in 4 weeks!" Was a frequent joke around the city due to the inactivity of many officials upon being voted into their position. This left a majority of the decisions to the Secretary of the Interiors who worked 
#- hard to build the city infrastructure with the citizens.§0
§0
§0§lImportant Names: §0Pantostado1600, farley50, PeppermintPig, FriedrichHayek, Taargus_, Hummelwagen, Ogel6000, ckeep, Chemistry35, CatZombies, and 
#- Doymand.§0
§0
§0   The core group of players was very influential within the city. Whether they held office or not, they devoted many hours of time and effort into the city. Building factories, cleaning grief, coordinating construction; all of 
#- these things would not have been possible without these players.§0
§0
